1. Installing ECLIPSE:

   a. Download the most recent version of “Eclipse IDE for Java EE Developers”
      from http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/

   b. Install

   c. Open eclipse and add the following modules using Eclipse Marketplace under
      menu Help-> Eclipse Marketplace (you can use find to locate the package quickly)

      i. Subversive – SVN Team Provider
         After restart, open the SVN perspective and select the “SVNKit 1.8.10” for connector.
         If you misses the previous step, you can also install the connector by using Eclipse
         Install New software under Help-> Install New Software. Type following in “Work with:”
         http://community.polarion.com/projects/subversive/download/eclipse/5.0/update-site/

      ii.Modify eclipse.ini and add
         -Djsse.enableSNIExtension=false

   d. Jaspersoft Studio

   e. Apache IvyDE

   f. Add the Google Plugin using menu Help-> Install New Software. In “Work with:”, type
      the following and click Add.
      http://storage.googleapis.com/gwt-eclipse-plugin/release
      You will only need to check the “Google Plugin for Eclipse 4.3” module.

2. Installing additional packages:

   a. sudo apt-get install ant

   b. sudo apt-get install ivy